# 🍪 Cookie Manager — Full Selenium

## Goal
Build a Cookie Manager with Selenium-based Google login, multi-account rotation, auto-refresh, and integration with all yt-dlp commands across the app.

## Architecture

```mermaid
graph LR
    UI[Cookie Tab UI] --> CM[core/cookie_manager.py]
    CM --> SE[Selenium Login]
    CM --> CS[Cookie Storage<br>cookies/*.txt]
    CM --> RO[Account Rotator]
    VCut[Video Cutter] --> RO
    YTDl[YouTube Downloader] --> RO
    RO --> CS
```

## Proposed Changes

---

### Core Module

#### [NEW] [cookie_manager.py](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/core/cookie_manager.py)

**Account storage** (`cookies/accounts.json`):
```json
[
  {
    "email": "user@gmail.com",
    "proxy": "",
    "cookie_file": "cookies/user_gmail_com.txt",
    "status": "live",
    "last_login": "2026-03-20T05:00:00",
    "use_count": 12,
    "last_error": ""
  }
]
```

**Key functions:**
- `load_accounts()` / `save_accounts()` — JSON persistence
- `login_account(email, proxy)` — Open Chrome via `undetected-chromedriver`, navigate to YouTube, user logs in manually, tool waits for login completion, exports cookies to Netscape format
- `check_cookie_status(cookie_file)` — Test cookie validity via yt-dlp `--cookies` + `--dump-json` on a known video
- `get_next_cookie()` — Round-robin rotator, skips dead accounts
- `refresh_dead_accounts()` — Re-login accounts with status "dead"
- `extract_from_browser(browser)` — Extract cookies from installed browser (Chrome/Edge/Firefox)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Uses `undetected-chromedriver` (pip install) instead of raw Selenium to bypass Google's automation detection. User still needs to handle CAPTCHA/2FA manually in the opened browser window.

**Cookie format**: Netscape HTTP Cookie File ([.txt](file:///f:/1.%20Edit%20Videos/8.AntiCode/2.Script_Split_Chapter/prompts/system_regroup.txt)) — compatible with `--cookies` flag in yt-dlp.

